Discriminant analysis of morphometric characters of the males of analysed taxa, showed that several characters: the ratio relative dorsal length P­ 4 /P­ 3 , relative dorsal length of P­ 4 , and relative dorsal length of P­ 2 , significantly contribute to discrimination of taxa on the first axis. Therefore they should be treated as stable characters for taxonomic use (
Fig. 9
).
